bitField.name: N
bitField.description: Negative condition flag.

bitField.name: Z
bitField.description: Zero condition flag.

bitField.name: C
bitField.description: Carry condition flag.

bitField.name: V
bitField.description: Overflow condition flag.

bitField.name: SS
bitField.description: Software step. Indicates whether software step is enabled.

bitField.name: IL
bitField.description: Set to 1 to indicate that on exception return, or as a result of an explicit change of the CPSR mode field in AArch32, an illegal state or mode was indicated.

bitField.name: D
bitField.description: Process state D mask. When the target exception level of the debug exception is higher than the current exception level, the exception is not masked by this bit.

bitField.name: A
bitField.description: Asynchronous abort mask bit. This bit has no effect on any Data Abort exception generated by a Watchpoint debug event, even if that exception is a synchronous.

bitField.name: I
bitField.description: IRQ mask bit.

bitField.name: F
bitField.description: FIQ mask bit.

bitField.name: nRW
bitField.description: Register width.

bitField.name: M
bitField.description: The current mode. For AArch64: M[3:2] holds the Exception Level. M[1] is unused, and returning to an exception level that is using AArch64 with this bit set is treated as an illegal exception return. M[0] is used to select the SP (0 means use SP0; 1 means the exception SP is determined by the EL).

register_group.name: Control
register_group.description: Displays status and Controls floating-point extension behaviour

bitField.name: AHP
bitField.description: Alternative half-precision control bit:

bitField.name: DN
bitField.description: Default NaN mode control bit: The value of this bit only controls VFP arithmetic. Advanced SIMD arithmetic always uses the Default NaN setting, regardless of the value of the DN bit.

bitField.name: FZ
bitField.description: Flush-to-zero mode control bit: The value of this bit only controls VFP arithmetic. Advanced SIMD arithmetic always uses the Flush-to-zero setting, regardless of the value of the FZ bit.

bitField.name: RMode
bitField.description: Rounding Mode control field. The encoding of this field is: The specified rounding mode is used by almost all VFP floating-point instructions. Advanced SIMD arithmetic always uses the Round to Nearest setting, regardless of the value of the RMode bits.

bitField.name: Stride
bitField.description: From ARMv7, ARM deprecates use of nonzero values of the Stride and Len fields. The values of these fields are ignored by the Advanced SIMD extension.

bitField.name: Len
bitField.description: From ARMv7, ARM deprecates use of nonzero values of the Stride and Len fields. The values of these fields are ignored by the Advanced SIMD extension.

bitField.name: IDE
bitField.description: Input Denormal exception trap enable. Possible values are: This bit is supported only in VFPv2, VFPv3U, and VFPv4U; it is RAZ/WI on a system that implements VFPv3 or VFPv4. The values of this bit controls only VFP arithmetic. Advanced SIMD arithmetic always uses untrapped exception handling, regardless of the value of this bit.

bitField.name: IXE
bitField.description: Inexact exception trap enable. Possible values are: This bit is supported only in VFPv2, VFPv3U, and VFPv4U; it is RAZ/WI on a system that implements VFPv3 or VFPv4. The values of this bit controls only VFP arithmetic. Advanced SIMD arithmetic always uses untrapped exception handling, regardless of the value of this bit.

bitField.name: UFE
bitField.description: Underflow exception trap enable. Possible values are: This bit is supported only in VFPv2, VFPv3U, and VFPv4U; it is RAZ/WI on a system that implements VFPv3 or VFPv4. The values of this bit controls only VFP arithmetic. Advanced SIMD arithmetic always uses untrapped exception handling, regardless of the value of this bit.

bitField.name: OFE
bitField.description: Overflow exception trap enable. Possible values are: This bit is supported only in VFPv2, VFPv3U, and VFPv4U; it is RAZ/WI on a system that implements VFPv3 or VFPv4. The values of this bit controls only VFP arithmetic. Advanced SIMD arithmetic always uses untrapped exception handling, regardless of the value of this bit.

bitField.description: Division by Zero exception trap enable. Possible values are: This bit is supported only in VFPv2, VFPv3U, and VFPv4U; it is RAZ/WI on a system that implements VFPv3 or VFPv4. The values of this bit controls only VFP arithmetic. Advanced SIMD arithmetic always uses untrapped exception handling, regardless of the value of this bit.

bitField.name: IOE
bitField.description: Invalid Operation exception trap enable. Possible values are: This bit is supported only in VFPv2, VFPv3U, and VFPv4U; it is RAZ/WI on a system that implements VFPv3 or VFPv4. The values of this bit controls only VFP arithmetic. Advanced SIMD arithmetic always uses untrapped exception handling, regardless of the value of this bit.

bitField.name: N
bitField.description: Negative condition flag. This is updated by floating-point comparison operations.

bitField.name: Z
bitField.description: Zero condition flag. This is updated by floating-point comparison operations.

bitField.name: C
bitField.description: Carry condition flag. This is updated by floating-point comparison operations.

bitField.name: V
bitField.description: Overflow condition flag. This is updated by floating-point comparison operations.

bitField.name: QC
bitField.description: Cumulative saturation bit, Advanced SIMD only. This bit is set to 1 to indicate that an Advanced SIMD integer operation has saturated since 0 was last written to this bit.

bitField.name: IDC
bitField.description: Input Denormal cumulative exception bit. This bit is set to 1 to indicate that the Input Denormal exception has occurred since 0 was last written to this bit. How VFP instructions update this bit depends on the value of the IDE bit. Advanced SIMD instructions set this bit if the Input Denormal exception occurs in one or more of the floating-point calculations performed by the instruction, regardless of the value of the IDE bit.

bitField.name: IXC
bitField.description: Inexact cumulative exception bit. This bit is set to 1 to indicate that the Inexact exception has occurred since 0 was last written to this bit. How VFP instructions update this bit depends on the value of the IXE bit. Advanced SIMD instructions set this bit if the Inexact exception occurs in one or more of the floating-point calculations performed by the instruction, regardless of the value of the IXE bit.

bitField.name: UFC
bitField.description: Underflow cumulative exception bit. This bit is set to 1 to indicate that the Underflow exception has occurred since 0 was last written to this bit. How VFP instructions update this bit depends on the value of the UFE bit. Advanced SIMD instructions set this bit if the Underflow exception occurs in one or more of the floating-point calculations performed by the instruction, regardless of the value of the UFE bit.

bitField.name: OFC
bitField.description: Overflow cumulative exception bit. This bit is set to 1 to indicate that the Overflow exception has occurred since 0 was last written to this bit. How VFP instructions update this bit depends on the value of the OFE bit. Advanced SIMD instructions set this bit if the Overflow exception occurs in one or more of the floating-point calculations performed by the instruction, regardless of the value of the OFE bit.

bitField.name: DZC
bitField.description: Division by Zero cumulative exception bit. This bit is set to 1 to indicate that the Division by Zero exception has occurred since 0 was last written to this bit. How VFP instructions update this bit depends on the value of the DZE bit. Advanced SIMD instructions set this bit if the Division by Zero exception occurs in one or more of the floating-point calculations performed by the instruction, regardless of the value of the DZE bit.

bitField.name: IOC
bitField.description: Invalid Operation cumulative exception bit. This bit is set to 1 to indicate that the Invalid Operation exception has occurred since 0 was last written to this bit. How VFP instructions update this bit depends on the value of the IOE bit. Advanced SIMD instructions set this bit if the Invalid Operation exception occurs in one or more of the floating-point calculations performed by the instruction, regardless of the value of the IOE bit.
